    <body>
        <h1>Caesar Salad</h1>
        <img src="https://www.shutterstock.com/image-photo/chicken-salad-caesar-grilled-croutons-600nw-1666973557.jpg">
        <h2>Description</h2>
        <p>This is a simple recipe for a healthy caesar salad. Feel free to add additional toppings like shredded carrot, 
            cherrub tomatoes, almond slices, or whatever else you'd like
        </p>

        <h2>Ingredients</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Romaine Lettuce</li>
            <li>Croutons</li>
            <li>Parmesan Cheese</li>
            <li>Caesar Dressing</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Steps</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>Wash and chop Romaine lettuce into bite-sized pieces</li>
            <li>In a large bowl, combine the chopped Romaine lettuce, croutons, and Parmesan cheese</li>
            <li>Add the Caesar dressing to the salad and toss until the ingredients are well coated. Add dressing gradually to achieve your desired level of flavor</li>
            <li>If you're including grilled chicken, bacon, or other optional additions, add them to the salad at this stage</li>
            <li>Serve the Caesar salad immediately and enjoy your delicious and classic creation!</li>
        </ol>
    </body>
